tafsir[2]{c,v,t}:
  40,1,"Ḥā Mīm. The discussion on similar letters has already passed in Sūrah Al-Baqarah."
  40,4,"No one disputes about Allah’s signs that indicate to His Oneness and the truthfulness of His messengers except those who reject Allah due to their deficient intellects. Do not grieve over them and do not let the abundant provision and favours that they enjoy deceive you. Their being given respite is a means of gradually luring them into their own destruction."